@node "Intr" "Introduction"
You've  seen  this before, gIZMO/ULTIMA and LSD have both written
doors that stop users from hitting the 1-5 keys etc. This  is  my
own personal version...msgbase safe.

Several  features  available  via  tooltypes.  Has the ability to
send an EALL/drop user from line/change axs level.

A private message to sysop will always be sent, but the  rest can
be switched off.

Password at mainline (if correct) will  allow  a  user  into  the
famous five situation. A small menu for their delight.

Plus it looks pretty funky.

This  is  really  a waste of time as in this day and age no sysop
should use the 1-5 keys. Use OPUS to  scan  your  callerlogs  etc
and  if  you want to send users files then go on a local node and
put them online in a 'requests'  conference!  They  can  download
them in a safer way. End of 'I'm ya mutha' speech;)
@endnode
